---

## 🔹 Kubernetes Essential Commands (with 1-line use)

```bash
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
```

→ Creates or updates the Deployment (runs pods)

```bash
kubectl apply -f service.yaml
```

→ Creates or updates the Service (exposes pods)

```bash
kubectl apply -f .
```

→ Applies all Kubernetes YAMLs in the folder

```bash
kubectl get deployments
```

→ Shows all deployments and replica status

```bash
kubectl get pods
```

→ Lists running pods and their health

```bash
kubectl get svc
```

→ Lists services and exposed ports

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```

→ Shows application logs from a pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```

→ Shows pod events, env vars, and errors

```bash
kubectl scale deployment foodhub-api --replicas=3
```

→ Scales the app to 3 running pods

```bash
kubectl scale deployment foodhub-api --replicas=0
```

→ Stops all pods without deleting deployment

```bash
kubectl delete deployment foodhub-api
```

→ Deletes deployment and all its pods

```bash
kubectl delete service foodhub-api
```

→ Deletes service and removes external access

```bash
kubectl delete -f .
```

→ Deletes all Kubernetes resources from YAMLs

